==English==

===Alternative spellings===
* [[Hypy]]

===Etymology===
From the prefix ''[[ent-]]'' meaning “within”, Greek ''ri'', and Latin ''[[nomen]]''

===Adjective===
'''Hyphy'''

# Rambunctious, loud, crazy, dangerous, irrational, and outrageous behavior.
#: ''She was so '''hyphy''' outside the club Saturday night, she nearly punched a cop!''
# Rambunctious, loud, silly, uninhibited, goofy, eccentric and odd behavior.
#: ''He had some weed at the party and was acting hella '''hyphy''' and weird.''
# A Northern California and mostly the Bay Area variation of the Crunk (or Krunk) rap music genre.
#: ''Keak da Sneak is probably the best '''hyphy''' artist to come out of the East Bay.''
# A song by rap artists Mac Dre and E-40.
#: ''I love singing that song '''Hyphy'''!''
# An energy drink from the Xcienece company.
#: '' '''Hyphy''' tastes so good mixed with vodka''

